Now this is not to say one way to say something is always the correct way. After all language keeps evolving, and if enough people make the same "mistakes" when speaking or writing it eventually ends up in a dictionary.
I'm mind blown at the "correct" way of saying these words I think these mistakes in my vocabulary come from a lack of needing to write them down and the people I learned them from.

Last but not least Example #3 is the last realization I have had and what truly inspired this post. So the electric power tool used by many construction workers to cut holes in walls is NOT called "saw saw" it's actually called sawzall!!

I blame the following 2 on my dad. Ok, Example #3: The little round things that go along with nuts, bolts and screws I ALWAYS thought they were called "Wasas" they are actually called WASHERS. Who would name a fastener and a home appliance the same thing?! Makes no sense
Example #1: "Bisteck" is not an actual English word. It comes from Spanish speakers pronouncing Beef Stake!! WHAT?!? I always thought bisteck and brisket were variations of the same thing

BRO!! Ok so story time. I have been pronouncing/writing things in English "wrong" my entire life because I learned English in a Spanish speaking community where these types of errors are overlooked. Recently, I have been finding out how some words are actually written or said.
